An Act relative to the pesticide board.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 3 of chapter 132B of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition,
2 is hereby amended by striking paragraph 5 and inserting in place thereof, the following
3 paragraph:-
4 The board, in addition to other powers conferred in this chapter, shall advise the
5 commissioner of food and agriculture with respect to the implementation and administration of
6 this chapter. The commissioner of food and agriculture shall consult and concur with the
7 commissioner of environmental protection and commissioner of public health when rendering a
8 decision under section 13 of this chapter, relative to the protection of groundwater sources of
9 drinking water from pesticide contamination.
